President Joe Biden welcomes the Houston Astros, the 2022 World Series Champions, to the White House. He thanks the team for their achievements and acknowledges their support for causes such as raising awareness on domestic violence and helping children with cancer. Biden praises the Astros for their community involvement, particularly in supporting the people of Uvalde, Texas, after a devastating event. He emphasizes the impact that sports teams can have on bringing hope and unity to communities. The team owner, Jim Crane, and manager, Dusty Baker, also speak, expressing gratitude for the invitation and highlighting the teamwork and perseverance that led to their championship win. The Astros present President Biden with a special gift, an Astros jersey.